'''Guia''' is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[List of parishes of Portugal|parish]] in the municipality of [[Albufeira]]. It has a population of 3,630 (as of 2001) and an area of 18.45&nbsp;km<U+00B2>. It is approximately 5&nbsp;km from the coast. The nearest beaches are Laurenco and Gale.

It is famous for its numerous piri-piri restaurants. Situated on the N125 (the principal east to west road on the Algarve with the exception of the A22 Motorway) it is a busy but nevertheless attractive place.

Sir [[Cliff Richard]] has a villa and vineyard just outside the village.

